linter friendly formatting here would be:
```
func (b *BtcWallet) GetBlockHeader(
	blockHash *chainhash.Hash) (*wire.BlockHeader, error) {

	return b.chain.GetBlockHeader(blockHash)
}
```

The linter only looks at new code, so that's why this triggers. Can just remove the argument name (`blockHash`) as we're not using the value anyway. Then everything should fit on one line easily:
```
func (*mockChainIO) GetBlockHeader(*chainhash.Hash) (*wire.BlockHeader, error) {
	return nil, nil
}
```
